ZH: 昨天我草草地写完了一本报告。
EN: Yesterday I hastily finished writing a report.

ZH: 她草草地穿上衣服，匆匆离开了家。
EN: She hurriedly put on her clothes and left home.

ZH: 我不能草草地决定，我需要仔细考虑。
EN: I can't make a hurried decision, I need to think carefully.

ZH: 他拿出了一块草草写的纸条。
EN: He took out a hastily written note.

ZH: 为了赶时间，我草草地吃完了午饭。
EN: I hastily finished my lunch to save time.

ZH: 他们的婚礼很草草，没有什么仪式感。
EN: Their wedding was done hastily, without much ceremony.

ZH: 我给他草草回了一封电子邮件。
EN: I hastily replied to his email.

ZH: 她穿得邋遢不整，梳头草草地就出门了。
EN: She dressed sloppily, quickly combed her hair and left.

ZH: 他带着草草打包的行李匆匆赶上了火车。
EN: He hurriedly caught the train with his hastily packed luggage.

ZH: 在他来访之前，我草草地打扫了一下房间。
EN: Before his visit, I quickly tidied up the room.

ZH: 他总是草草地完成工作，不注重细节。
EN: He always does his work hastily, without paying attention to details.

ZH: 这个项目的计划太草草了，没有经过充分的准备。
EN: The project's plan was too hastily made, without sufficient preparation.

ZH: 他草草地读完了这本书，没有悉心品味。
EN: He hastily finished reading this book without savoring it.

ZH: 他写了一份草草地写的道歉信，没有真诚的表达。
EN: He wrote a hastily written apology letter, without sincere expression.

ZH: 为了赶上飞机，他草草地收拾好行李。
EN: To catch the plane, he hastily packed his luggage.

ZH: 这个建议是草草提出的，没有经过深思熟虑。
EN: This suggestion was hastily put forward, without careful consideration.

ZH: 他完成任务非常草草，没能达到预期的质量要求。
EN: He completed the task very hastily, failing to meet the expected quality requirements.

ZH: 她在考试前只是草草地复习了一下，所以成绩不理想。
EN: She only hastily reviewed before the exam, so her grades were not ideal.

ZH: 我们不应该草草了事，应该认真对待每个问题。
EN: We shouldn't handle things hastily, we should take every issue seriously.

ZH: 他写了一篇草草的演讲稿，没有充分准备。
EN: He wrote a hastily prepared speech, without sufficient preparation.
